So far, from what I've read, Flower armour seem to be the best for us MAs. Its tailored to our skills and seems to provide more protection than similarly QL other armours.<br>
Am I right on this?<br>
<br>
MA suits.<br>
Ok someone has to explain the logic behind this.<br>
The main Ability for an MA suit is Stamina. Howerver, the MA skill does not use Stamina. Why oh why would I dump IP into stamina if I don't need it. (yes, I do put some in, but not Maxed like Agility and Strength)<br>
Yes I know that some suits give MA, Brawl and a few other skills as a bonus BUT the IP I need to dump into stamina can easily be put into the MA abilities or treatment for bigger implants.<br>
I currently wear an MA suit and have had to beg for Stamina buffs to put on a higher lvl suit.<br>
So, my question is:<br>
Are MA suits worth it? If not, are there any other suits that are more tailored to an MA base skills?<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
Orpo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ikagawa>Ikagawa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#660000>(1/16/03 8:30:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2163.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.insightbb.com/~claybats/images/avatars/mt_11.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armour and MA suits</span><hr size=1> So far as I've played my MA, I've always kept my Stamina maxed. It directly relates to your hp and other skills (can't remember off the top of my head). Of course, my MA is Solitus and yours could be Opifex in which case we would play differently seeing as how your Stamina is dark blue.<br>
<br>
I've always had him in an MA suit if I could keep him in one. They give great protection, as well as raising some skills (depending on what color you get).<br>
<br>
If I remember correctly, you keep Psy and Sen maxed, right? If that's the case, then you should use a Red or Turquoise (think it's Turquoise) since they're Sense/Agi or Int/Psy respectively.<br>
<br>
You may not be able to roll for them as mish rewards (which I hear you can do with other cloaks), but you find them much more frequently as boss loot than other cloaks as well.<br>
<br>
PS: Corrections please, I'm probably wrong about my suggestions somewhere ^_^ <p>Bellerephon<br>
